  "instructions": [
    "Heat oil in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat.",
    "Add lamb and cook until browned, about 5 minutes. Remove lamb and set aside.",
    "Add onions and cook until caramelized, about 8 minutes.",
    "Add garlic, ginger, cumin, smoked paprika, cinnamon, turmeric, and cayenne pepper. Cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add lamb back to the pot and stir to combine.",
    "Add broth and bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours or until lamb is tender.",
    "Stir in Gruyère cheese until melted and smooth.",
    "Season with salt and pepper to taste.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with chopped parsley if desired.",
    "Serve with gluten-free couscous or rice.",
    "Note: Traditionally, a clay tagine is used to cook this dish. If you have one, use it! Otherwise, a Dutch oven will work just fine."
